name: galactokinase
classes: Phosphotransferases with an alcohol group as acceptor
comment: Part of the Leloir pathway for galactose metabolism. The enzymes from mammals and from the bacterium Escherichia coli have no activity with N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine [4-6].
